    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-12-03T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-12-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="517"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d517">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">891.6363/12–344: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Iran</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Morris</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tehran</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-12-03">December 3,
                            1944</date>.<lb/>[Received December 7—1:08 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>895. The Majlis yesterday received and enacted during the same session the
                    following introduced by Dr. Mossadegh.<note n="90" xml:id="d517fn90">Mohammed
                        Mossadegh, Deputy in the Majlis.</note>
                </p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“Article 1. No Prime Minister or Minister or Acting Minister or Under
                        Secretary of State may undertake any official discussions or discussions
                        having a local character or sign any agreement regarding a petroleum
                        concession with official or unofficial representatives of neighboring or
                        distant governments or with representatives of oil companies or with any
                        other person.</p>
                    <p>Article 2. The Prime Minister and the Ministers may undertake negotiations
                        for the sale of petroleum and with regard to the manner in which the Iranian
                        Government is to exploit and administer its oil wells; the Majlis must
                        however be informed of the progress of the negotiations.</p>
                    <p>Article 3. Any person or persons violating the above provisions will be
                        sentenced to from 3 to 8 years of imprisonment and will be permanently
                        debarred from Government office.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Sent to Department repeated to Moscow, London, Cairo, Baghdad.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
